Description: In our Differentiation Atlas,non-osteoblastic cells are potentially osteogenic-capable cells.
Osteoblasts, Regulated by Sp7 and Runx2 (10.1016/j.bone.2020.115458),  are the masterminds behind bone formation, sculpting the intricate architecture of the skeletal system.

Chondrocytes, marked by the high expression of Sox9 and Acan, exhibit a remarkable capacity for osteogenesis, as evidenced by in vivo observations at various developmental stages, while lineage tracing studies employing Col2a have unequivocally confirmed their osteogenic potential.(10.1038/ncb3067)

Mainly found in long bones, expressing genes like Fn1 and S100a4. (10.1016/j.cell.2019.04.040)Its potential osteogenic ability has been reported in some literature.(10.7554/eLife.54695,10.1016/j.stem.2017.02.009) Its homogeneity with mesenchymal cells is also currently under extensive scrutiny.(10.1002/jcp.26860,10.1016/j.acthis.2020.151634,10.1159/000445096)

The key component of BMSC enriched in diaphysis of long bone, with its osteogenic potential confirmed(10.1016/j.stem.2014.06.008), expresses fat-related genes such as Adipoq. However, it lacks traditional fat markers and does not contain lipid droplets. In some literature, it is considered an essential cell for maintaining the bone marrow vascular system and suppressing bone formation.(10.7554/eLife.54695).In the literature, these are often annotated as BMSC , dpBMSC(10.1016/j.celrep.2021.109352) and Adipoq+ MSC .

The population exhibiting high expression of Ly6a was notably present during the fetal stage in the head and limb regions (Figure 2d), as described in previous studies (10.3389/fcell.2021.656999). It is marked as extracranial mesenchyme in the skull, guiding the migration of early osteogenic cells and assisting in the establishment of suture boundaries (10.1038/s41467-021-24917-9). In the limb bud, it may serve as a skeletal progenitor (10.3389/fcell.2021.656999).

This cluster exhibits high expression of Prrx1 in embryonic cranial bones and limb buds. It can originate from either the mesoderm or neural crest lineages. Its osteogenic capability has been confirmed through lineage tracing involving Prrx1 (10.1016/j.stemcr.2017.03.002, 10.1038/s41588-022-01227-4).

This cluster highly expressed Rgs5. It is not excluded from Differentiation Atlas because it is reported to be associated with osteogenesis (10.3390/ijms20051079). Some literature annotations refer to it as pericyte(10.1016/j.celrep.2022.111045), while others classify it as a smooth muscle cell.(10.1002/advs.202201273)
High expression of Col1a1 and Acan, the hypertrophic cartilage transitions toward ossification state, as revealed by tracking with Col10a1.(10.7554/eLife.76932)

This cluster was annotated following the reference (10.1016/j.cell.2019.04.040). They typically express Grem1 (10.1016/j.cell.2019.04.040) and Pthlh (10.1038/s41586-018-0662-5), which are associated with osteogenesis in the resting zone of the growth plate.

The transitional state between cartilage and mesenchyme, co-expressing Col2a1 and Prrx1, was identified during lineage tracing of Col2a1 (10.1101/2020.03.13.990853). This transitional state exhibited specific expression of Cyp26a1.

Early mesenchyme with high expression of proliferation genes (Top2a) can be observed in both craniofacial and limb development, predominant during the organogenesis stage (E8.5-E14) (10.1101/2020.03.13.990853), indicating that it does not have neural crest/mesodermal source specificity. It can be defined as an early osteodermal progenitor or perichondrium in the literature (10.1016/j.celrep.2020.107871, 10.1101/2020.03.13.990853).

Mainly found in long bones, expressing genes like Fn1 and S100a4. (10.1016/j.cell.2019.04.040)Its potential osteogenic ability has been reported in some literature.(10.7554/eLife.54695,10.1016/j.stem.2017.02.009) Its homogeneity with mesenchymal cells is also currently under extensive scrutiny.(10.1002/jcp.26860,10.1016/j.acthis.2020.151634,10.1159/000445096)

This cluster is typically located within the growth plate and undergoes dedifferentiation to form bone. It exhibits high expression of the Col10a1 gene. Its osteogenic differentiation ability has been confirmed through lineage studies involving Col10a1 (10.1073/pnas.1302703111).

This cluster exhibits high expression of Col2a1 and Hmmr in both long bones and limb buds. In the literature, they are annotated as proliferating and resting chondrocytes (10.1016/j.cell.2019.04.040). Some studies have demonstrated their long-term osteogenic potential (10.1016/j.jgg.2023.04.004). It also shows high expression of Dlx5, which is an important source of osteogenesis in early periosteal cells (10.1038/s41467-022-34804-6).

Predominantly present within cranial sutures, this cluster is marked by Irx1 and expresses Lef1 and Inhba. It is located on the outer periphery of suture-associated osteogenic cells and is considered to possess potential osteogenic capabilities (10.1038/s41467-021-24917-9).
Most of them, during E14-E18, can be labeled as late  osteodermal progenitor in the literature.(10.1016/j.celrep.2020.107871,10.)
Mainly found in long bones, with high expression of Fxyd2 and Acan, they may be involved in the maturation process of cartilage

Meningeal cells exist in the skull, with high expression of Fxyd5, among others. They show more markers associated with arachnoid and dura mater than markers associated with pia mater.(10.1038/s41467-021-24917-9)
Most of them, during E11-E15, can be labeled as intermediate  osteodermal progenitor in the literature.(10.1016/j.celrep.2020.107871,10.)
The precursors of osteoblasts are commonly found in various tissues, with high expression of Postn and Mmp13.
High expression of Tex14 and Erg2, the hypertrophic cartilage transitions toward ossification state, as revealed by tracking with Col10a1.(10.7554/eLife.76932)
Specifically present in the growth plate, possibly located in the upper zone. Expressing A2m, Ucma,Grem1.(10.1002/jbmr.3719)
Subpopulation of Lepr+ BMSC.
Expressing stem cell genes such as Ly6a, Cd34, and Thy1, it is also considered by some literature to be the primary source of osteogenesis in adult bone marrow.(10.7554/eLife.54695)
This group of cells with high expression of Bglap3 may represent the most mature osteoblasts.

A less mature subpopulation of osteoblasts.In long bone, it characterized by the expression of Clec11a, the integrin ligand periostin (Postn) and the Notch pathway gene Hey1.(10.1016/j.celrep.2021.109352). It's also located around blood vessels, serving as a mechanical pressure sensor and possessing strong bone-forming capabilities.
The subpopulation of Lepr+ MSCs that express lipid markers such as Fosb and Cebpb are considered to be preadipocytes.(10.1016/j.celrep.2019.06.031)
The main subpopulation of pre-osteoblast.
High expression of Ffar4 in a subpopulation of hyperchodnrocyte.

High expression of Foxa2, Ihh, within the hypertrophic chondrocyte subpopulation, present in limb buds and long bones, expressed adjacent to secondary ossification centers, and confirmed to possess osteogenic capability
Specifically expresses Kcnk2, also expresses osteogenic genes like Postn. It may be in a transitional state between Lepr+ MSCs and pre-osteoblasts.
Subpopulation of osteoblasts with high expression of Sost.
High expression of Ostn in a subpopulation of pre-osteoblasts.
High expression of Sstr2, considered by some studies to be the source of stem cells in the metaphysis of long bones.(10.1101/2022.09.08.506930)
High expression of Prg4 and Grem1, presumed to be precursors of cartilage, is annotated as chondrocyte progenitors in some articles.(10.1016/j.cell.2019.04.040)

They are found in both long bones and cranial bones, expressing low levels of Acan and Mia, and are considered as precursors of cartilage. In cranial bones, they are typically annotated as chondroblasts.(10.1016/j.celrep.2022.111045)In long bones, they are located in the resting zone, exhibit high expression of Pthlh, and are considered an important source of osteogenesis.(10.1038/s41586-018-0662-5)
Defined within the cranial sutures and annotated as suprasutural mesenchyme, characterized by the gene C1qtnf3.(10.1038/s41467-021-24917-9)

MSCs that gather at the metaphysis of long bones, characterized by the expression of Clec11a, the integrin ligand periostin (Postn) and the Notch pathway gene Hey1.(10.1016/j.celrep.2021.109352). It's also located around blood vessels, serving as a mechanical pressure sensor and possessing strong bone-forming capabilities.(10.1038/s41586-021-03298-5)

Defined within the cranial sutures and annotated as Ligament-like mesenchyme, exhibiting high expression of tendon formation-related genes such as Scx, Tnmd, Mkx, Thbs2, and Bgn.(10.1038/s41467-021-24917-9)

They are considered to be hypertrophic pre-chondrocytes initiating the maturation process, expressing Ihh, Pth1r, and Mef2c, annotated as Chondrocytes-prehypertrophic in some paper.(10.1016/j.cell.2019.04.040)
